<br>
For this thread, I would appreciate it if you'd keep your comments to one line and one line ONLY....I'll only be keeping this thread open for about five days or so to get a general feeling of which of the following methods you guys would prefer to use.  The real vote, when its called for, might be choosing between two systems rather than just a list of rules for us to say yes or no to.<br>
<br>
No one need comment about how none of this is enforcable.  We all know that.  But we also know that Brell has a tradition of respecting the wishes of the community as a whole.  That's why I'm asking these questions.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Would you prefer that POG be:<br>
<br>
RESERVABLE: Under a system such as what we presently use for fear/hate/sky.<br>
<br>
-or-<br>
<br>
FIRST COME, FIRST SERVED (FCFS): Meaning that whichever raid group reached the plane first with a valid raiding force (oh, call it, 24 people), would have rights to the plane (or whatever portion of the plane they desired) for the duration of their raid.  That group could 'share' the plane with other groups who arrived if they so desired, but would be under no obligation per server rules to do so.<br>
<br>
-or-<br>
<br>
FREE FOR ALL (FFA): Meaning, you get your raid group, you zone in, you kill what you want to kill.  If there are 180 people comprising six different &quot;raids&quot; in there, then so be it.  Whatever you aggro, you get to beat on.  This is not to say there would be no compromising under this system.  I'm quite sure there would be.  But no one would ever have &quot;rights&quot; to the plane or any section of the plane.  This is not to say that you could not post &quot;intentions&quot; to raid growth, but no one on the server would be under any circumstances obligated to respect said intentions.<br>
<br>
JUST SO THERE IS NO CONFUSION -- THIS IS NOT A RULE MAKING VOTE.  THERE ARE NO RULES TO BE APPROVED/DISAPPROVED IN THIS THREAD.  THOSE WILL COME AFTER I FIGURE OUT WHAT, EXACTLY, YOU GUYS WOULD LIKE TO DO ABOUT THIS PLANE. <p><BR>
